# Skill: Persistence Safety (Frontend)

## Goal
Handle browser persistence safely and consistently.

## Placement
- All shared storage wrappers must live in `src/storage/`.
- Do not put persistence utilities in `src/lib/`.

## Rules
- Guard browser-only APIs (`window`, `localStorage`, `sessionStorage`).
- Expose typed read/write helpers.
- Keep storage modules free of UI logic and network logic.
- If persistence is needed by multiple modules, create/update a storage wrapper instead of inline storage access.

## Non-Applicable Backend Rules
- DB transactions, unit-of-work, and outbox patterns are not applicable in this frontend repo.
- Do not add backend transactional abstractions here.

## Checklist
- [ ] Storage code in `src/storage/`
- [ ] SSR-safe guards are present
- [ ] Types exported for stored payloads
- [ ] No UI/network imports in storage module
